data.meta_description: "Wahrnehmung ist falschnehmung." FRANZ BRENTANO (Januari 16, 1838 - 1917); Prussian philosopher and psychologist whose work strongly influenced his students Sigmund Freud, Kazimierz Twardowski, Alexius Meinong, and Thomas Masaryk (as well as Masaryk's student, Edmund Husserl), and countless others whose work would follow and make use of his original ideas and concepts.
